org.jlinalg.field_p

Class FieldPLong

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jlinalg.RingElement<RE>
      • org.jlinalg.FieldElement<RE>
        • org.jlinalg.field_p.FieldP<FieldPLong>
          • org.jlinalg.field_p.FieldPLong
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<FieldPLong>, IRingElement<FieldPLong>

    class FieldPLong
extends FieldP<FieldPLong>
    This class implements the operations in Fp where p < PRIME_SEPARATION_BOUNDARY. All computations can be done using long variables. IMPORTANT: This class and its subclasses make use of the concept of immutability of objects. If you make changes or subclass these classes, ensure immutability or overwrite the methods affected.
    Author:
    Lochbihler Andreas, Georg Thimm

    • Constructor Detail

      • FieldPLong

        FieldPLong(long value,
           FieldPAbstractFactory<FieldPLong> factory)
        Returns a new element of the field Fp. The element is the equivalence class containing value. This method should only be called by the factory FieldPAbstractFactory
        Parameters:
        value - The new element is the equivalence class of value. This value is assumed to be in the range of 0..(p-1).
        factory - the factory producing elements in Fp (typically the caller of this constructor).
